    <data key="d0">MagellanTV Content Localization Pipeline</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UPV6ggX4eSE</data>
    <data key="d2">MagellanTV automates content localization for thousands of hours of documentaries across different distributors. The architecture processes video content by performing multi-stage ML translations, including idiom detection, sentence shortening, and cultural checks using Amazon Bedrock, followed by text-to-speech with Amazon Polly and human quality review with A2I. Amazon Step Functions orchestrates the entire workflow, which is deployed and scaled using AWS CloudFormation (via CDK) to handle large volumes of content efficiently, reducing processing costs from $20 to $1 per minute.</data>
    <data key="d3">data_ingestion, compute_intensive, control</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
